HEADWORD: Au gratin
<hw>Au` gra`tin"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>With a crust made by browning in the oven,
especially by sprinkling with bread crumbs or grated cheese and browning
in a broiler; <as>as, spaghetti may be served <ex>au
gratin</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

